p.font: Zombies move around guided by the smell of humans. The direction they choose in each iteration of the simulation is given then by humans' position distribution combined with their smell. The better nose a zombie has, the more sensitive it is to humans who are closer to him. Mathematical formulation of this rule is similar to gravitational potential formalism. In a way, zombies are moving inertly within the field of gravitational-like potential generated by humans. They always go in the direction of gradient (fastest growth) of that field.
